##Hospital in Wuchang is seriously infected and supplies are still in short supply

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to break through the fog, to find the truth, to watch the Times.

"He's a hero. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At 10:54 am on February 18, the director of Wuchang Hospital, Liu Zhiming, died at the age of 51 after being infected with new crown pneumonia.

"Liu is a very responsible person with a strong heart, and our colleagues at the hospital respect him very much. He was very tall, very talented, and it was very unpleasant to say no,"Qiu Jiangping, a nephrologist at Wuchang Hospital, told China News Weekly.

At present, the health care workers in Wuchang Hospital are seriously infected, involving a number of departments and departments, including the director and head nurse. At the same time, the hospital is facing a shortage of materials, still outside help. The current supplies, such as protective clothing, can last only three to five days, the director of the Wuchang Hospital's docking donation office told China Newsweek.

The difficulty of transformation

On January 21, Wuchang Hospital was notified to become one of the first designated hospitals in Wuhan to issue fever outpatient clinics. That day at 5:00 p.m. , Liu Zhiming called his old colleague Jin Jie and informed him of the news. How to renovate the hospital has become the most urgent task, the construction period is too short, only two days to vacate and renovate.

This is the last time the two exchange, Liu Zhiming did not mention his physical condition. Jin Jie is the former director of the third people's Hospital in Wuhan. Prior to his appointment as director of Wuchang Hospital, he worked with Jin Jie for many years at the third people's Hospital in Wuhan. Jin Jie was impressed by Liu Zhiming's enthusiasm and ability. As director of the hospital, he transformed the Wuchang Hospital from a second-class one to a third-class B hospital.

But for this transformation, Jin Jie also some uncertainty, time is too short, not to mention, there were more than 800 patients in Wuchang Hospital.

At 4 a.m. on Jan. 22, Liu Zhiming was still at work. He called his wife, Cai Liping, and said he could not go home after the hospital had finished its renovation. The wife is a little anxious, ask the husband why so late still do not rest. The next afternoon, the wife received the news that her husband had contracted pneumonia and was hospitalized. Cai Liping recalled that her husband had a low-grade fever for a week as early as mid-january.

In the ward transformation process, Qiu Jiangping heard that President Liu was hospitalized, a variety of occasions also disappeared president's figure. It was a tight schedule, a one-day deadline, almost impossible to complete, and a lack of continuity to deal with.

Qiu Jiangping is well aware of the necessity of ward reform. Before the transfer to designated hospitals, Wuchang Hospital materials and equipment shortage, there is no special staff access, does not have the conditions to deal with infectious diseases. "When we were in the fever clinic, the corridor was full of people coming in and out, so we wore protective clothing inside the clinic and went straight to see the patient, and as soon as we took off the protective clothing, we had to step out of the crowd of patients, " Qiu told China Newsweek.

Qiu Jiangping's nephrology department had more than 60 hemodialysis patients, 22 days all transferred to hospital. According to his introduction, these patients were first transferred to Tianyou Hospital, but on January 29, Tianyou hospital also became the third designated hospital, these hemodialysis patients had to be transferred again.

On January 24, the 30th anniversary of Lunar New Year, Wuchang Hospital began to receive new patients with coronary pneumonia. That night, the nurse Xu Wen on duty, then feel too many patients, all of a sudden poured in. She was not familiar with the layout of the ward after the renovation, looking for a long time to find the passage of medical staff, passing through, saw in the aisle in the smoked wormwood.

Several nurses interviewed expressed concern about the cleaning area. Hospital conditions are limited, wards are located on the first and second floors, corridor between the ventilation. Half of the third floor is where medical staff rest and wear off their protective gear, while the other half is also the patient's hospital ward, separated by a passageway about two meters wide. Every time we go to the cleaning area, we go through this tunnel, and there's a window in the partition, and it's open.

Meanwhile, Liu Zhiming's condition worsened. Cai Liping, the head nurse in the intensive care unit (ICU) of Wuhan's Third Hospital, Guanggu Hospital, was also busy with pneumonia patients and had seen him on her breaks. More often than not, she learned from her husband's attending physician that his oxygen saturation was below 80 and he couldn't get it up.

The hospital infection is getting worse

When Qiu and his colleagues began treating hemodialysis patients with the new pneumonia on Feb. 2, the needs of this particular group had become apparent. But we're still short-staffed, with four doctors, 10 dialysis machines, and 30 dialysis patients. At the same time, colleagues around the infection is getting worse.

At the end of January, Wuchang Hospital had arranged for medical staff to carry out a unified CT examination, Qiu Jiangping in the C2 ward there are two nurses with signs of pneumonia, was arranged isolation. The first floor has been cleared out of the way to accommodate the hospital's staff who are suffering from new pneumonia.

At the end of January, nurse Zhang Ting had just been transferred to the inpatient department, where she worked in general surgery, to take charge of patients with new pneumonia. After the CT results came out, Zhang Ting heard that several nurses in the ICU were infected. She was a little worried about the working conditions, and she was short-staffed, didn't have enough shifts, and worked hard all the time.

In addition, supplies are also very tight, the next morning after the night shift, Zhang Ting was told that only instant noodles can be eaten. She spoke to the head nurse, but there was nothing she could do.

More and more colleagues have taken off their protective clothing and become patients in the wards. The head of the Pharmacy Department was seriously ill with pneumonia. The head pediatric nurse and four nurses were also infected with the virus. In addition, the infection was serious in departments that had little contact with patients, such as the personnel department, which puzzled Zhang and other nurses.

At 7 am on February 6, Liu Fan, a 59-year-old nurse, felt unwell and had fever. She called the head nurse of the department. Liu worked in the injection room of the Lei Yuen Street Community Health Service Centre at Wuchang Hospital. She was admitted to the hospital the next day after being diagnosed with the infection.

Meanwhile, Liu Zhiming's condition is still deteriorating. On February 4, he put a vacuum in the intensive-care unit. His wife finally dialed his phone, put forward to accompany, Liu Zhiming refused, worried about infection to his wife. In the Wechat chat with his wife, Liu Zhiming mentioned his physical condition, "Hypoxia, irritability, body sweating. "

Jin Jie learned that friends in the hospital, had to call Liu Zhiming several, but has been shown off. The director of the intensive-care unit at Wuchang Hospital told him that Liu's condition was serious and he developed symptoms on January 19.

On February 14, Liu Zhiming was transferred from the intensive-care unit of Wuchang Hospital to the Central Court district of Tongji Hospital for oxygen intubation. On the same day, a nurse, Liu Fan, died of pneumonia after being resuscitated. Liu's parents and younger brother had died of pneumonia. A colleague of nurse Zhang Ting once worked with Liu fan, impression is"a very active and diligent old comrade".

Li Taisheng, the leader of the Peking Union Medical College Hospital's second team, took part in the rescue effort. He later said that oxygen intubation was a more effective method for treating patients with severe new coronary pneumonia, but in more than two days after the intubation, Liu Zhiming's condition did not significantly improve.

On Feb. 17, the medical team gave Liu an ECMO, and he later developed ventricular fibrillation. The next day, the medical team for Liu Zhiming heart ultrasound examination, found that "in addition to the lungs are very bad, the heart is thrombus, heart and lungs in a state of serious failure. ".

Liu Zhiming died at 10:54 a.m. on Feb. 18. "He was the first Dean to die in the battle against the plague, " Jin told China News Weekly. "He fought on the front line and gave his life. As his colleague, I would say he was a hero. "

World Health Organization (WHO) director-general Tan Desai expressed his condolences to Wuhan Wuchang Hospital Director Liu Zhiming for his death due to new crown pneumonia Sunday through social media, Xinhua reported. Tan Desai expressed his deepest condolences to Liu Zhiming's family and colleagues. "during the outbreak of the new crown pneumonia, Dr. Liu Zhiming was moved and saved countless lives, " he said. "My heart goes out to them and all the medical staff who are fighting the virus on the front lines. ".

(at the request of the interviewee, Qiu Jiangping, Zhang Ting and Xuwen County were all pseudonyms.)
